The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
Archives
 The City Diary
																																																		Pritam Das, 11, and five of his friends were injured in a blast while playing in the compound of an abandoned oil mill in Palpara, in the airport police station area, on Thursday afternoon. The police said Pritam noticed a can behind a bush when he went there to fetch a ball. As soon as he lifted the can, it exploded. All six were taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital.																																																		Cops from the detective department rounded up more than 6,000 people from different parts of the city in the past couple of weeks. An officer said all those who have been picked up have criminal records. Raids will be continue during the Puja, he added.																																																		One person was killed and 15 were injured when the Matador they were travelling on collided with a bus on Council House Street on Thursday morning. The drivers were arrested.																																																		An unidentified, middle-aged man was injured after being knocked down by a vehicle at the Beleghata Main Road-EM Bypass crossing on Thursday afternoon. The man was admitted to NRS Medical College and Hospital. 
